<title>USA: Bethlehem sees Q2 gain from Iron Ore sale.</title>
<headline>Bethlehem sees Q2 gain from Iron Ore sale.</headline>
<dateline>BETHLEHEM, Pa 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bethlehem Steel Corp on Tuesday said it expected to record an after-tax gain of $113 million, or $1.01 per share, in the second quarter from the sale of its 37.57 percent equity interest in the Iron Ore Co of Canada.</p>
<p>The company sold the stake to North Ltd, an Australian diversified resources concern. Bethlehem said the sale should bring cash proceeds of about $145 million.</p>
<p>As part of the transaction, National Steel Corp sold its 21.73 percent equity interest in the Iron Ore Co of Canada to North Ltd.</p>
<p>&quot;Bethlehem's sale of its interest in the Iron Ore Co of Canada is a continuation of its corporate strategy of concentrating on its core steel businesses and rebuilding its financial strength,&quot; the company said in a statement.</p>
</text>
